Anteater Chess - Alpha Release
ChessEaters, EECS 22L, UC Irvine
April 2026
Version 1.0 (Alpha)

Authors: Shawn Harrington, Claire Lin, Jordan Le, Tara Pai, Yani Montanez, Aurea Juarez

Anteater Chess is a modified version of chess played on a 10x8 board with two extra
pieces called Anteaters. The goal is to checkmate the opponent's king. The program
supports user vs user, user vs AI, and AI vs AI matchups with a chess clock and
difficulty selection.

To install, type "make". For detailed instructions see INSTALL.
For how to play, refer to doc/Chess_UserManual.pdf.
